snippet.textDisplay: braaaaad babe, noooo, I KNOW you don't think dreads are matted hair. A dreadlock is a LOCK of the curl, if your hair is curly (and I mean a tighter curl, thinking type 3 and up range) then it can FORM that lock, it's the curls locking together. If your hair is straight, then YES it's MATTING, that's not a dreadlock that's a matter strand of hair babe. Dreadlocks are not gross, they're not unhealthy, theyre healthy, beautiful hairstyles worn by extraordinarily confident people who keep them despite knowing how many rude comments theyll get from people.
